ion of the events. The\nassociation with heat flux and beta is generally consistent with the whistler\nfan instability although there are intervals where the heat flux is\nsignificantly lower than the instability limit. Strong scattering of strahl\nenergy electrons is seen in association with the waves, providing evidence that\nthe waves regulate the electron heat flux..\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 11 Sep 2020 19:25:04 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 27 Sep 2020 16:34:37 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 14 Dec 2020 23:14:10 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-06-02"}
