ar to\nthat in the cuprates, but the value of the Hund's coupling $J_H$ is found to be\nsensitive to the Nd magnetic moment. The exchange coupling $J$ in NdNiO$_2$ is\nonly half as large as in the curpates, which may explain why $T_c$ in the\nnickelates is half as large as the cuprates.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 12 Sep 2020 15:50:59 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-06-14"}
